ode_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-10-07T14:41:51Z","updated_at":"2025-10-07T14:41:51Z","body":"# So what behaviour do we actually want?\n\n## Simple case without generators\n\n**simple example without setup/teardown code**\n```cpp\nTEST_CASE(\"foo\") {\n    SECTION(\"A\") {\n        SECTION( \"B1\" ) {\n            REQUIRE(true);\n        }\n        SECTION( \"B2\" ) {\n            REQUIRE(true);\n        }\n        SECTION( \"B3\" ) {\n            REQUIRE(true);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n`./tests \"foo\"`\n -- 3 assertions\n\n`./tests \"foo\" -c \"A\"`\n -- 3 assertions, cause \"A\" is there and we don't filter further\n \n`./tests \"foo\" -c \"A\" -c \"B\"`\n -- 0 assertions, cause \"B\" is not there\n\n`./tests \"foo\" -c \"A\" -c \"B1\"`\n -- 1 assertion, because B2, B3 do not match\n\n`./tests \"foo\" -c \"A\" -c \"B2\"`\n -- 1 assertion, because B1, B3 do not match\n\n`./tests \"foo\" -c \"A\" -c \"B2\" -c \"XXX\"`\n -- 1 assertion, the extra filter is not an issue\n\nHow to run B1 and B2 without B3? You cannot, you have to run the test twice.\n  -- Possible extension in the future, to have something like -c \"B*\", or \"B1,B2\", similar to test spec matching\n\n\n**Assertions outside main section (simulates set up and tear down)**\n```\nTEST_CASE( \"bar\" ) {\n    REQUIRE( true );\n    SECTION( \"A\" ) {\n        SECTION( \"B1\" ) { REQUIRE( true ); }\n        SECTION( \"B2\" ) { REQUIRE( true ); }\n        SECTION( \"B3\" ) { REQUIRE( true ); }\n    }\n    REQUIRE( true );\n}\n```\n\n`./tests \"bar\"`\n -- 9 assertions\n\n`./tests \"bar\" -c \"A\"`\n -- 9 assertions, cause \"A\" is there and we don't filter further\n\n`./tests \"bar\" -c \"A\" -c \"B1\"`\n -- 3 assertions, cause only 1 of the 3 subsections of A are run\n\n`./tests \"bar\" -c \"XXX\"`\n -- 2 assertions (set up, tear down, A is not entered)\n\n`./tests \"bar\" -c \"B1\"`\n -- 2 assertions (set up, tear down, A is not entered)\n\n`./tests \"bar\" -c \"A\" -c \"B1\" -c \"B2\"`\n -- 3 assertions (set up, tear down, the path is A -> B1 -> then there are no further sections\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/3377222760/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/3377410774","html_url":"https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2/issues/3038#issuecomment-3377410774","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/3038","id":3377410774,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABA2rM7JTzLW","user":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-10-07T15:20:23Z","updated_at":"2025-10-07T15:20:23Z","body":"## With Generators\n\n* Generators are an implicit section, that starts at their location and lasts until the end of the scope.\n* Generators currently cannot be filtered. This is intended to change.\n\n**Simple example without setup/teardown code**\n```cpp\nTEST_CASE(\"baz\") {\n    SECTION(\"A\") {\n        REQUIRE(true);\n    }\n    auto _ = GENERATE(1, 2, 3);\n    SECTION(\"B\") {\n        REQUIRE(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n`./tests \"baz\"`\n -- 4 assertions\n\n`./tests \"baz\" -c \"A\"`\n -- 1 assertion, but note that it still enters the test case **3 times**\n\n`./tests \"baz\" -c \"A\" -c \"B\"`\n -- 1 assertion, but note that it still enters the test case **3 times**\n\n`./tests \"baz\" -c \"A\" -c \"XXX\"`\n -- 1 assertion, but note that it still enters the test case **3 times**\n\n`./tests \"baz\" -c \"B\"`\n -- 3 assertions\n\n`./tests \"baz\" -c \"XXXXX\"\n -- 0 assertions, but note that it still enter the test case **3 times**\n\n\n**Assertions outside top level sections**\n```cpp\nTEST_CASE(\"qux\") {\n    REQUIRE( true );\n    SECTION( \"A\" ) {\n        REQUIRE( true );\n    }\n    auto _ = GENERATE( 1, 2, 3 );\n    SECTION( \"B\" ) {\n        REQUIRE( true );\n    }\n    REQUIRE( true );\n}\n```\n\n`./tests \"qux\"`\n -- 12 assertions\n\n`./tests \"qux\" -c \"A\"`\n -- **7 assertions**\n\n`./tests \"qux\" -c \"B\"`\n -- 9 assertions, 3 from section \"B\", 6 from setup and teardown for every generator element\n\n`./tests \"qux\" -c \"B\" -c \"XXXX\"`\n -- 9 assertions, 3 from section \"B\", 6 from setup and teardown for every generator element\n\n`./tests \"qux\" -c \"XXXXX\"`\n -- 6 assertions, 0 from sections, 6 from setup and teardown as the generator still has to run through elements\n\n\n**Dynamic sections in a generator**\n```cpp\nTEST_CASE( \"corge\" ) {\n    REQUIRE( true );\n    SECTION( \"A\" ) {\n        REQUIRE( true );\n    }\n    auto i = GENERATE( 1, 2, 3 );\n    DYNAMIC_SECTION( \"i=\" << i ) {\n        REQUIRE( true );\n    }\n    REQUIRE( true );\n}\n```\nThis behaves similarly to the previous example with single important\ndifference, which is that we can run the generator's subsection for just\n1 element:\n\n\n`./tests \"corge\" -c \"i=2\"`\n -- 7 assertions, 1 from the dynamic section when generator returns 2,\n    6 from setup and teardown as the generator iterates its 3 elements.\n\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/3377410774/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/3402297953","html_url":"https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2/issues/3038#issuecomment-3402297953","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/3038","id":3402297953,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABA2rM7KyvJh","user":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar","html_url":"https://github.com/horenmar","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-10-14T14:59:03Z","updated_at":"2025-10-14T14:59:03Z","body":"**Generator inside a sibling section**\n\nThis provides a nice way of only running the first section, or only\nrunning the generator inputs. Generators are still unfiltered however,\nso setup and teardown code inside section \"B\" runs a lot, even if the\ndynamic section will never be entered.\n\n```cpp\nTEST_CASE(\"grault\", \"[approvals]\") {\n    REQUIRE( true );\n    SECTION( \"A\" ) {\n        REQUIRE( true );\n    }\n    SECTION(\"B\") {\n        auto i = GENERATE( 1, 2, 3 );\n        DYNAMIC_SECTION( \"i=\" << i ) {\n            REQUIRE( true );\n        }\n    }\n    REQUIRE( true );\n}\n```\n\n`./tests \"grault\"`\n -- 12 assertions (4x setup and teardown, 1 in A, 3 in B)\n\n`./tests \"grault\" -c \"A\"`\n -- 3 assertions (1x setup and teardown, 1 in A)\n\n`./tests \"grault\" -c \"B\"`\n -- 9 assertions (3x setup and teardown, 3 in B)\n\n`./tests \"grault\" -c \"B\" -c \"i=1\"\n -- 7 assertions (the generator has to run 3 times, but only 1 time the dynamic section is entered)\n\n`./tests \"grault\" -c \"B\" -c \"XXX\"\n -- 6 assertions (the generator still has to run 3 times, but no dynamic section is entered)\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catchorg/Catch2/issues/comments/3402297953/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"horenmar","id":9026413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwMjY0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9026413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/horenmar